Program: Discovery
Title: The Copernicus theory
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx0s
Last Broadcast Date: 24 November 1997
Predicting the future using Copernicus theory. Using the theories of Nicolaus Copernicus that the location of anything is unlikely to be special, using probability to guide us as to what our future is. Also why fingerprints hold clue to sexual identity and designing artificial blood cells. Presenter: Graham Easton. Show less